Remember:
- You can only trade one share at a time
- You have limited time to trade
- Setting "now": true will execute at the best available price
- Orders can be canceled before they are fulfilled
- trade using the private signal in the winning market since the public signal is likely distorted
- you can never have more offers to sell shares (asks) than the number of tax shares in your wallet
- The sum of the prices of your offers to buy shares (bids) can never exceed the balance in your wallet
- If your outstanding asks or bids exceed the limits in your wallet, you should cancel the order that is furthest from the median price in the market
